title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger SR9C
postcontent:
Purchased a while ago, never used, NIB. 
Looking to sell or trade.
This one has the stainless steel slide.
Here's the info:
The SR9c compact pistol weighs in at 23.40 oz. and features an overall length of 6.85", a height of 4.61", and the same slim 1.27" grip width (across safety levers) as the full-sized SR9. It comes with two magazines that provide options in both capacity and grip size. The standard magazine holds 10 rounds and features a flat bottom butt plate; a finger grip extension floor plate is also included. The second magazine features a grip adapter and holds 17 rounds, instantly transforming the smaller, compact grip into a full-sized 9mm grip. The 3.50" barreled pistol features an integral accessory rail that accommodates most lights and lasers.

The SR9c compact pistol utilizes the same adjustable, high-visibility 3-Dot sight system as its full-sized predecessor, setting it apart from many compact pistols that rely on fixed sights. New serrations are located on the front portion of the slide, making it easier to both manipulate the slide and to press check the chamber. The SR9c is available with a glass-filled nylon frame and through-hardened slide in either a brushed stainless or black nitrite finish. 

Just like the original, full-sized SR9, the SR9c is loaded with modern safety features like a 1911-style ambidextrous manual safety, internal trigger bar interlock and striker blocker, trigger safety, magazine disconnect, plus a visual and tactile loaded chamber indicator.

title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER PARKER REPRODUCTION -- DHE 12-GAUGE SxS...26, IC/M, SST...
postcontent: Here's a high quality shotgun for someone seeking a classic upland double. This is a Parker Reproduction that was manufactured under contract with Winchester at the Olin-Kondesha plant in Japan. These guns were only manufactured for about 4 years but were of extremely good quality, in fact the parts are interchangeable with original late production Parkers! Some would argue that these are actually of better quality than the originals due to improvements in steel alloys and the chrome lined barrels which were not used in the old guns. This example is a DHE grade chambered in 12-gauge. While the 12-gauge is the most common bore in the original Parkers, not so with the Parker Reproductions where the 12-gauge is actually the most scarce (twice as many 28-ga guns were made, and 3x as many 20's). This gun is built on the 1-1/2 sized frame and wears 26" barrels with two beads. The chambers are 2-3/4" and the barrels are choked Improved Cylinder & Modified. It features Ejectors, a Single-Selective Trigger, and automatic safety. The receiver is engraved and has a case color finish. The barrels are rust blue in the traditional manner. The wood has pleasing figure and cut checkering. The pistol grip buttstock has a skeleton buttplate and there is a beavertail forend. LOP measures 14-1/8"; D@H is 2-1/4"; D@C is 1-1/4". Overall condition is quite good with some moderate wear and handling from use. The case colored finish is strong on the receiver and screws are untouched. The finish on the barrels rates about 97-98% with a few minor marks but no rust, pitting, or dents. The stocks are sound and free of any cracks or chips. There are some normal handling marks as one would expect in a gun that has seen some light use in the field. There are no large dings, dents, gouges or ugly scratches although there are a series of very small shallow dents along the upper right side of the butt. Mechanically excellent with nice bright bores. It comes in the original factory supplied case with outer canvas/leather cover and includes the original snap-caps as well. This would appear to be a nice early example...serial number 12-00046.

title: For Sale:  S&W 629-4 Classic 6.5" - .44 Mag
postcontent:
Up for trade is a Smith & Wesson Mod. 629-4 Classic chambered in .44 Magnum. It is a 6-shot n-frame revolver with a 6.5 inch barrel and S&W labeled hogue rubber grips (RB). This Mod. 629 has the -4 designation which is the last dash model that is pre-lock and pre-MIM (forged hammer & trigger) revolver with the complete factory Endurance Package. The endurance package was created in response to silhouette shooters who were using heavy bullets loaded as fast as possible. S&W simply beefed up these revolvers to last a lot longer and to be able to take more of a beating. It entails as follows: hardened hand & bolt, hardened retention system on the yoke/cylinder crane, hardened yoke and frame, radius-ed internal studs, and elongated bolt cuts on the cylinder.

I would consider this to be in great condition with very good lock up, perfect timing, and excellent cylinder-forcing cone gap. If you want a Smith & Wesson .44 magnum you will NOT be disappointed with this one! It comes with its original factory box/papers and 25 rds of 240 gr Winchester soft points ("Deer & Black Bear").

I would be interested in other smaller caliber (.38/.357) S&W revolvers and 1911's. I may be interested in others, just ask. Even trades or with cash my way only. Price is $950 $900 in the Murfreesboro area.

Gun is located in the Central/Middle TN area. Must be 21 years old, a Tennessee resident, and not a convicted felon. Drivers License required, HCP preferred.

postcontent: Here's a very nice Winchester Model 61 pump rifle. Chambered for the .22 Short, Long or Long Rifle, this Winchester wears the original 24" round barrel with factory iron sights. According to available serial number information, this Model 61 was manufactured in about 1956. Overall, a very nice example!

title: For Sale:  Belgium .22 (or 6mm) Flobert rifle
postcontent: This Belgium .22 (or 6mm) Flobert rifle was made around 1890 to 1920 and sold as a boys rifle.  At the time, it was the European equivalent of the Red Ryder BB gun that we all know so well.  It is a single shot, breach loading rifle with a range of about 15 yards.  The bullet it was designed to shoot was essentially just a .22 cal lead ball propelled by a primer only.  The ammo today, is considered exotic but is still easily obtainable by special order from gun shops.  I've rated this rifle to be in Fair to Good condition due to the fact that the rear sight is missing, otherwise, this rifle is in good condition.  There is no rust damage, and it is fully functional with the proper ammo but I wouldn't shoot it!  Cash only sale.
